headlines.description: — The Memphis Grizzlies pummeled the Brooklyn Nets with hammers and daggers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Luke Kennard scores season-high 25 points, Grizzlies beat Nets 106-102 to end 5-game skid

headlines.description: — Not even the absence of Giannis Antetokounmpo could cool off the Milwaukee Bucks.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bucks don't have Antetokounmpo but still beat Clippers 113-106 for 6th straight victory

events.name: Portland Trail Blazers at Minnesota Timberwolves

headlines.description: — Rudy Gobert had 25 points and 16 rebounds for his 43rd double-double of the season, Michael Conley added 19 points and seven assists, and the Minnesota Timberwolves completed a four-game season sweep of Portland, beating the Trail Blazers 119-114...
headlines.shortLinkText: Rudy Gobert and Michael Conley power Timberwolves past Trail Blazers 119-114

headlines.description: — Jordan Clarkson scored a season-high 38 points, including a 12-0 run down the stretch, to boost the Utah Jazz over the Washington Wizards 127-115 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Jordan Clarkson scores 38 as Jazz pull away late to beat Wizards 127-115

headlines.description: — Coby White had a career-high 37 points and DeMar DeRozan scored 19 of his 33 in the fourth quarter as the Chicago Bulls rallied from 22 points down to beat the Sacramento Kings 113-109 on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: White scores career-high 37 as Bulls rally from 22 down to stun Kings 113-109

events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — D’Angelo Russell hit five 3-pointers while scoring 26 points, and Anthony Davis added 24 points and 12 rebounds in the Los Angeles Lakers' 116-104 victory over the Oklahoma City Thunder on Monday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: D'Angelo Russell scores 26 points, leads surging Lakers past West-leading Thunder 116-104
